	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><persName>Judah&#39;s</persName> Death</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>May 31st</date> <add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your pens are execrable<add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#38; I can scarcely write with them.<lb/> Your letter of the <date>30th</date> had just<lb/> been received&#59; Mamma says<lb/> that she thinks &#8220;<persName>Mr. <hi rend="underline">Judah&#39;s</hi></persName><lb/> <hi rend="underline">Will is shameful &#38; she never</hi><lb/> heard of anything so unjust.&#8221;<lb/> We are sorry to hear that you<lb/> have caught another cold&#44; you<lb/> should be more careful.<lb/> Two more letters have been re&#45;<lb/>ceived from <persName>Mr. M. M. Allen</persName>&#59; in<lb/> one of them he wished to know<lb/> whether you intended leaving<lb/> town this week&#44; &#38; desired to know<lb/> immediately&#44; as otherwise he would<lb/> not come here to read on <date>Saturday</date><lb/> so I wrote him a few lines telling<lb/> him that you had gone&#44; I</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>suppose that it will be all right<lb/> Mamma took the note herself&#44; &#38;<lb/> handed it to <persName>Mr. A. T. Jones</persName> at his<lb/> office&#44; &#38; then she went to see the<lb/> girls &#38; found them looking very<lb/> well&#59; they send their love to you.<lb/>  There are letters here from <persName>Mr<lb/> Allen</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr M. Isaacs</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr Louis<lb/> Solomon</persName> &#38; <persName>J. N. Cardozo</persName>.</p>
				<p><persName>Mr Allen</persName> sends a copy of the<lb/> proceedings of the &#8220;Board of dele&#45;<lb/>gates&#8221;.  <persName>Mr. Isaacs</persName> officially<lb/> informs you that you were<lb/> unanimously reelected Vice Presi&#45;<lb/>dent&#59; <persName>Mr Hart</persName> was chosen President<lb/> in place of <persName>Judge Cardozo</persName> who<lb/> was absent &#38;c.  A resolution<lb/> was unanimously adopted to<lb/> the effect that the absence of<lb/> <persName>Rev I. Leeser</persName> occasioned by the<lb/> death of a relative&#44; was deeply<lb/> regretted by the <sic>conreation</sic><add>&#63;</add>.<lb/>  <persName>Mr Louis Solomon</persName>&#44; <placeName>Southfield Ogn.</placeName><lb/> wishes to know the price of the<lb/> &#8220;Family Bible&#44;&#8221; also the price of<lb/> a <hi rend="underline"><add>&#63;</add> sett</hi> of prayers according</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>to the German minhag&#44; English<lb/> &#38; Hebrew&#59; he encloses a stamp<lb/> so I intend to send him an<lb/> answer&#44; but your sets of prayers<lb/> are all Portuguese.</p>
				<p><persName>Mr Cardoza</persName> sends an advertise&#45;<lb/>ment for the &#8220;Occident.&#8221;</p>
				<p>This is all I believe.</p>
				<p>If you wish it I can send you<lb/> <persName>Mr Isaac&#39;s</persName> letter when I <add>&#63;</add>&#44;<lb/> unless you fear it may get lost.<lb/>  <persName>Aunt &#38; Uncle <add>&#63;</add>ash</persName> are coming<lb/> today so I shall not have much<lb/> time to translate&#44; &#38; more over it<lb/> is <hi rend="underline">awfully hard <sic>german</sic></hi>.<lb/>  Things go on here as usual.<lb/>  <persName>Mr Jones</persName>&#39; son called for the<lb/> books.  The large Bible for<lb/> <hi rend="underline"><add>&#63;</add></hi>&#44; has been sent here&#59;<lb/> what is to be done with it&#63;<lb/>  Mamma&#39;s eyes trouble her very<lb/> much&#44; but she looks<add>&#63;</add> better to&#45;<lb/>day.</p>
				<p>We received a letter from <persName>Uncle Sam</persName><lb/> on <date>Monday</date>&#59; they are all well with</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>the exception of <persName>Mary<add>&#63;</add></persName> who is<lb/> again sick.</p>
				<p><persName>Jesse Nashes<add>&#63;</add></persName> wife&#44; <persName>Clara</persName>&#44; is<lb/> dead&#59; she died last <date>Tuesday</date><lb/> is it not very sad&#63;</p>
				<p>This letter is <add>&#63;</add> so good bye<lb/> Mama &#38; <persName>Delia</persName> send Love &#38;<lb/> a <hi rend="underline">little <add>&#63;</add></hi> comes from</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">L. L. Lazarus</persName></p>
				<p>Write soon</p>
		</body>
